17/01/2010
ZAGREB, Croatia -- Two explosions hit an oil refinery in the central town of Sisak late on Saturday (January 16th) causing a fire in the fuel processing unit of the facility owned by the INA oil group. Initial reports said there were no injuries, and the scale of material damage is not yet clear. The unit had been out of operation for the past couple of days due to technical problems. (HRT, Reuters - 16/01/10)
